 "notes":"Two-generation history: the 2026-07-06 Next.js globals.css establishes the app shell with an explicit light/dark pair (light bg #ffffff / fg #171717; dark bg #0a0a0a / fg #ededed via prefers-color-scheme) using Geist Sans/Mono. The richer 2026-07-08 Figma import (Dovizir/MVP, 51,588 nodes) is the authoritative source and wins on conflicts: it supplies the real palette, Roboto/Poppins/Inter type matrix, 60 component sets / 537 variants, radii, spacing, shadows and motion. Both modes are retained additively — light surfaces (#FFFFFF/#F5F5F5/#F8F8F8) and dark surfaces (#121212/#272727/#2E2E2E/#383838) both ship. Semantic roles derived from usage: #2196F3 is the most-used color on Button/<Button> interactive names → primary; #90CAF9 is the accent tint used on dark-mode buttons; the dominant on-surface inks (#171717/#231F20 light, #EDEDED dark) → text; #4CAF50/#43A047 recur on positive helper/amount vectors → success; #E53935/#FF4B55 → error/warn; #FFB400 → warning; #E0E0E0/#E4E4E7 are the top stroke colors → borders. Component variant/state counts are grouped estimates apportioned from the global axis distribution (State 95, Size 113, Color 87, Disabled 26, etc.), not per-set exact figures. Fonts marked found only where literally present (Roboto/Poppins/Inter in Figma, Geist Mono in globals.css)."}